    "We additionally down-weigh less accurate predictions near t = 0 by applying a scaling factor of t p, p opt = 1 in the residual loss computation.",
    "A detailed analysis of different power laws is provided in Appendix D. The more accurate prediction of x 1 substantially improves the evaluation of the physics residual in eq. 2, which in turn yields a better learning direction.",
    "A final aspect of key importance in physics based flow matching is the value of σ min, which denotes the amount of Gaussian noise added to the training data.",
    "In computer vision tasks, σ min is typically set to 10 -3 (Lipman et al., 2023; Esser et al., 2024).",
    "However, the introduction of Gaussian noise perturbs the physical residuals, degrading the model's performance."
